HEADWORD: Samara
<hw>Sa*ma"ra</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ ?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>samara</ets>, <ets>samera</ets>, the seed of the elm.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A dry, indehiscent, usually one-seeded, winged
fruit, as that of the ash, maple, and elm; a key or key fruit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

